<h2>Undergraduate Students</h2>
<p>I am a strong believer in research experiences for all undergrads. I have worked with more than 250 undergraduate students in the past decade. This has included undergraduate research and Senior Design projects. The emphasis is on open-ended, challenging projects.</p>
<p>Some of the senior design projects have led to actual products. Recent success stories include <a href="http://warp.rice.edu/trac/wiki/HardwareUsersGuides/FPGABoard_v2.2">WARP FPGA Board </a>and <a href="http://warp.rice.edu/trac/wiki/MAC">WARP MAC Framework</a>. More recently, the students have made great progress in biomedical devices, see <a href="http://sh.rice.edu/">Scalable Health Initiative</a>. If you are a Rice undergrad and interested in research opportunities at CMC, please write to me. We have projects available throughout the year and prefer students who are looking for multi-semester engagement.</p>
